msg: Some files still have ancient license headers, despite them being contributed under

Browsing the CruiseControl history clearly outlines that they imported Commandline
themselfs from *tataa*: Apache. The original autor states Stefan Bodewig.
Also the work/import of Trygve never had this license notice.
Others have their origins in maven-1 shared which is clearly ALv2 as well.
THUS: I got rid of all the unnecessary and unadequate license headers
and replaced them with the ALv2 header.
